The paper focuses on the structural properties of CFL functions, which are related to context-free languages. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses containments, separations, and refinements among various classes of functions, which are related to computational complexity. Hence, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also analyzes optimization functions, which are related to optimization problems, and their relationships to the associated languages, which are related to information theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories.
